{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1921a","heading":"Sole and exclusive authority of Board and Chief to determine rates of pay","label":"1921a Sole and exclusive authority of Board and Chief to determine rates of pay","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/ch29/schI/ptB","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1921a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection is from the Legislative Branch Appropriations Act, 2005, which is div. G of the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2005."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1921a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1921a%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The rate of basic pay (including the rate of basic pay upon appointment), premium pay, specialty assignment and proficiency pay, and merit pay.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t2/s1921a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft2%2Fs1921a%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The rate of cost-of-living adjustments, comparability adjustments, and locality adjustments.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":